# env — everything except the template. Per-network files (`.env.localnet`,
# `.env.testnet`, `.env.mainnet`) hold private keys and Enoki secrets, as
# does the `.env.local` mirror. `.env.*.local` catches Next.js's per-env
# local overrides (`.env.development.local`, `.env.production.local`,
# `.env.test.local`). `*.tmp` variants catch the temp files written by
# `scripts/use.ts` and `bootstrap.ts` between the write and the rename;
# an interrupt mid-flight can leave those on disk containing secrets.
.env
.env.*.local
.env.local
.env.local.tmp
.env.localnet
.env.localnet.tmp
.env.testnet
.env.testnet.tmp
.env.mainnet
.env.mainnet.tmp

